  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And by the good hand of our God upon us,.... Favouring their designs and orders, protecting those that were sent, and inclining those they were sent to use their interest and authority with those that were under them, and making them willing also to agree to what was proposed to them: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "they brought us a man of understanding of the sons of Mahli, the son of Levi, the son of Israel; an Israelite, of the tribe of Levi, in the line of Mahli a son of Merari, the third son of Levi: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and Sherebiah; or rather \"even Sherebiah\"; so Aben Ezra; for he is the understanding man that is meant, and described by his pedigree: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "with his sons and his brethren, eighteen; all together made this number. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "with his sons and his brethren, eighteen; all together made this number. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
